<description>This course will introduce and survey the genre of Latin letter writing through the reading of selected letters of Cicero and Pliny the Younger. The primary focus will be on reading epistolary Latin, but attention will also be given to issues of generic convention, self-presentation, and the physical realities of ancient letter production and circulation.</description>
